<Layout title="Dream Privacy Policy">
    <Navigation />
    <header>
		<div class="hero-elements main-content">
			<section class="header-text">
				<h1 class="page-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
			</section>
		</div>
	</header>
    <main>
		<section class="main-content policy">
            <h2>1. Introduction and Purpose</h2>

            <p>At Dream AI Labs Ltd. (referred to as "Dream," "we," "our," or "us"), we prioritize the security and privacy of our users’ (“you” or “your”) data. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal information while using our services. By accessing and using our services, you agree to the practices described in this Policy. We are dedicated to ensuring that your personal data and communications are kept safe and secure.</p>
            <p>For any questions or additional information, feel free to contact us at <a href="mailto:info@usedream.ai">info@usedream.ai</a>.</p>

            <h2>2. Scope of the Privacy Policy</h2>

            <p>This Privacy Policy applies to the use of our website and services, which are further described in our Terms of Service. It governs the collection, processing, and protection of all personal information gathered through Dream’s services.</p>
            <p>We define "Personal Information" as any data about an identifiable individual that is collected by us, except for aggregated data that cannot be used to identify an individual. The information we collect is used only for purposes described in this Policy.</p>

            <h3 style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 24px;">2.1. User Consent</h3>

            <p>By using our services, including our website and applications, you agree to this Privacy Policy and our Terms of Service, and you consent to the collection, storage, processing, and disclosure of your Personal Information as outlined here.</p>
            <p>If your organisation is subject to the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) (EU 2016/679), you may be required to sign or agree to a Data Processing Agreement with Dream to ensure full compliance when processing data within our services.</p>

            <h2>3. Collection of Personal Information</h2>

            <h3 style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 24px;">3.1. Information You Provide</h3>

            <p>When you register for Dream’s services, we collect certain personal details including your name, email address, physical address, and any other information necessary for account creation and service delivery. This information is vital to providing you with the service and ensuring secure communications.</p>

            <h3 style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 24px;">3.2. Information We Automatically Collect</h3>

            <p>Dream collects navigational information when you visit our website or use our services. This includes data like your IP address, browser type, operating system, geographical location, and how you interact with our platform. This helps us improve the user experience and enhance the functionality of our services.</p>

            <h3 style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 24px;">3.3. Payment Information</h3>

            <p>We use third-party, PCI-compliant service providers to collect and process payment information when you subscribe to our services. Dream does not store sensitive payment details such as credit card numbers. We only retain necessary billing information to maintain service functionality.</p>

            <h3 style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 24px;">3.4. Children’s Privacy</h3>

            <p>Our services are not intended for individuals under the age of 13. Dream does not knowingly collect personal data from children. If you believe that a child’s data has been collected, please contact us immediately at <a href="mailto:info@usedream.ai">info@usedream.ai</a>, and we will delete the information.</p>

            <h2>4. Use of Personal Information</h2>

            <h3 style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 24px;">4.1. Providing Services</h3>

            <p>We collect and process personal data to deliver the best possible service. This includes sending you relevant communication, notifications, and updates about our services. Dream may also use your information to personalise the service based on your preferences and past interactions.</p>

            <h3 style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 24px;">4.2. Marketing Communications</h3>

            <p>If you opt-in, Dream may send marketing communications, newsletters, or promotional offers that may interest you. You can unsubscribe from marketing emails at any time by clicking the “unsubscribe” link at the bottom of these emails or by contacting us at <a href="mailto:info@usedream.ai">info@usedream.ai</a>.</p>

            <h3 style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 24px;">4.3. Improving Our Services</h3>

            <p>We use aggregated and anonymized data, including navigational information, to analyse trends and improve the functionality and performance of Dream’s services. This helps us understand how users engage with the platform and allows us to refine the service accordingly.</p>

            <h3 style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 24px;">4.4. Legal Compliance and Security</h3>

            <p>We may disclose your personal information to comply with applicable laws, regulations, legal processes, or governmental requests. Additionally, we may use your data to investigate potential violations of our Terms of Service or to protect the safety and integrity of our platform and users.</p>

            <h2>5. Security of Personal Information</h2>

            <p>Dream employs a range of industry-standard security measures to protect your personal data from unauthorised access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. This includes using encryption, secure servers, and monitoring tools to safeguard your information.</p>
            <p>While we strive to protect your data, no system is entirely foolproof. You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials. If you suspect any unauthorised access or breach of your account, please notify us immediately.</p>

            <h2>6. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>

            <h3 style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 24px;">6.1. Cookies</h3>

            <p>Dream uses cookies to track your preferences and enhance your experience on our website. Cookies are small data files stored on your device that help us recognize you when you return to the site. You can adjust your browser settings to decline cookies, but doing so may impact the functionality of certain features.</p>

            <h3 style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 24px;">6.2. Web Beacons and Navigational Data</h3>

            <p>We also utilise web beacons (tracking pixels) to gather information about how users engage with our emails and services. This allows us to measure the effectiveness of our campaigns and improve service delivery. If you prefer not to be tracked, you can opt to disable images in your email client.</p>

            <h2>7. GDPR Compliance</h2>

            <p>For users in the European Economic Area (EEA), Dream is fully compliant with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). As a data controller, we ensure that your personal data is processed lawfully, fairly, and transparently.</p>

            <p>Your GDPR rights include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Right of access: You can request to see the personal data we hold about you.</li>
                <li>Right to rectification: You may correct any inaccurate or incomplete personal information.</li>
                <li>Right to erasure: You may request the deletion of your data, subject to legal obligations.</li>
                <li>Right to restrict processing: You may limit how we use your data.</li>
                <li>Right to data portability: We can provide your data in a commonly used format upon request.</li>
            </ul>

            <p>If you wish to exercise any of these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:info@usedream.ai">info@usedream.ai</a>.</p>

            <h2>8. Information Sharing</h2>

            <h3 style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 24px;">8.1. Third-Party Service Providers</h3>

            <p>Dream may share personal information with trusted third-party service providers to facilitate the delivery of our services (e.g., payment processors, hosting providers). All third parties are bound by confidentiality agreements and are only permitted to use your data to fulfil their services to us.</p>

            <h3 style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 24px;">8.2. Legal Requirements</h3>

            <p>We may share personal information if required to do so by law or in response to a valid legal process (e.g., court orders, subpoenas). Additionally, we may share data when necessary to protect the rights, property, or safety of Dream, our users, or others.</p>

            <h3 style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 24px;">8.3. Business Transfers</h3>

            <p>In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your personal information may be transferred to the acquiring company. You will be notified in advance if such a transfer affects your personal data.</p>

            <h2>9. Data Retention</h2>

            <p>We retain your personal data for as long as necessary to provide the service or as required by law. Once your account is closed, or if it becomes inactive, Dream will retain your information only for as long as needed to comply with legal obligations or resolve disputes.</p>

            <h2>10. Data Transfers</h2>

